= Bean Soup, Vegan

#columns(2)[
  == Equipment
  - Crock-pot
  - Food dehydrator
  - Knife
  - Sink & strainer (recommended)

  *Yields many servings.*

  == Ingredients

  === Pre-Broth
  - 115g (1 cup) celery
  - 900g (1 packet) dried beans

  === Broth
  - 2L water
  - 125g (1/2 cup) soy sauce
  - 40g (3 tbsp.) avocado oil
  - 480g (2 large) tomatoes, blended
  - 350g (2 medium) onions, diced
  - 160g bell peppers, diced
  - 30g (2 tbsp.) salt
  - 15g vegetable seasoning, unsalted
  - 12g seaweed, dry, crushed
  - 10g yeast flakes
  - 3 bay leaves
  - 1 pinch cumin

  === Afterwards
  - Ghost pepper (optional)#footnote[~Because capsaicin has a relatively low sublimation
      point, we introduce this at the very end.
    ]

  - Cilantro, diced, to taste

  #colbreak()

  == Steps

  === The Day Before

  - If beans are dry:
    + Rinse beans in cold water.
    + Add beans to large pot. Soak in water for at least 8 hours.
    + Repeat rinse.

  - If celery is *NOT* dry:
    + Leave celery in food dehydrator.

  === The Night Before

  + Add beans, ample water, and broth ingredients to crock-pot.
  + Set crock-pot to Low.
  + Shuffle celery in dehydrator, if applicable.
  + Go to bed, 8-10 hours.

  === The Day Of

  + Set crock-pot to Warm.
  + Cut & crush celery.
  + Mix celery & peppers into soup.
  + Serve hot with cilantro. Good with tortillas or other carbs.
]

== Trivia

This recipe was modeled off of @bean-soup[my earlier bean soup recipe], in haste for a
potluck on 18 Apr. 2026. This is perhaps most obvious in how much I go out of my way to
inject umami (soy sauce, celery, tomatoes, seaweed), since I normally expect it to come
free with the meat in my bean soup. The only reason it's vegan is so that I can give it to
some Seventh-Day Adventists, and the only reason it calls for a crock-pot is so that I can
go to bed soon.
